<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>9 SPEED AND 11 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTO-1X707LL/DLL/MLL AND RTO-1X709MLL MODELS - REMOVE - INPUT SHAFT
        ASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="6">
        <title>INPUT SHAFT ASSEMBLY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the six (6) retaining bolts and cover from the front bearing cover. Remove any
                remaining gasket material from the case and cover (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302056">Figure 56</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302056" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302056" filename="../figg13/G1302056.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 56. Remove Six Retaining Bolts</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the bearing retaining snap ring from the input shaft groove (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302057">Figure 57</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302057" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302057" filename="../figg13/G1302057.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 57. Bearing Retaining Snap Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a soft bar and maul to drive the input shaft toward the case rear as far as possible.
                Pull the input shaft forward (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302058">Figure 58</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302058" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302058" filename="../figg13/G1302058.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 58. Input Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use pry bars to complete removal of the bearing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302058">Figure 58</hotlnk>
                and
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302059">Figure 59</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302059" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302059" filename="../figg13/G1302059.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 59. Drive Gear Spacer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the drive gear spacer from the drive gear front (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302059">Figure 59</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the drive gear internal snap ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302059">Figure 59</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pull the input shaft forward and out of the drive gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302060">Figure 60</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302060" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302060" filename="../figg13/G1302060.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 60. Input Shaft Out Of Drive Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the drive gear from inside the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302060">Figure 60</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the bushing in the input shaft pocket and replace if necessary (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302061">Figure 61</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302061" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302061" filename="../figg13/G1302061.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 61. Inspect Bushing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
